Kenya like the rest of the countries in Africa will be celebrating World Environment Day tomorrow, June 5th. Representatives from around Kenya are coming together in Kwale to commemorate the international day with a tree planting ceremony. Several activities have been organized across the counties and here in Nairobi, the celebrations will be held at Kikuyu springs during which this years edition of the African Climate Change and Environmental Reporting Awards will be launched. This year's theme is ‘beat plastic pollution.’